cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it deals with deep neural network compression. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as DNNs are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as DNNs are a popular AI technique. The use of probabilistic data structures suggests it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
